quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,130,""
  26,131,""
  26,132,""
  28,76,"Verily, Qârûn (Korah) was of Mûsâ’s (Moses) people, but he behaved arrogantly towards them. And We gave him of the treasures, that of which the keys would have been a burden to a body of strong men. Remember when his people said to him: "
  28,77,""
  28,78,"He said: "
  29,43,"And these similitudes We put forward for mankind; but none will understand them except those who have knowledge (of Allâh and His Signs)."
  29,44,"(Allâh says to His Prophet Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  29,45,"Recite (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) what has been revealed to you of the Book (the Qur’ân), and perform As-Salât (Iqamât-as-Salât). Verily, As-Salât (the prayer) prevents from Al-Fahshâ’ (i.e. great sins of every kind, unlawful sexual intercourse) and Al-Munkar (i.e. disbelief, polytheism, and every kind of evil wicked deed){1} and the remembering{2} (praising) of (you by) Allâh (in front of the angels) is greater indeed [than your remembering (praising) of Allâh in prayers. And Allâh knows what you do.",footnotes:1:[ (V.29:45) It is said by Ibn ‘Abbâs and ‘Abdullâh bin Mas‘ûd رضي الله عنهم: If the Salât (prayer) of anyone does not prevent him from Al-Fâhshâ’ and Al-Munkar (all kinds of evil, illegal and sinful deeds), then his Salât (prayer) increases him in nothing but loss, and to be far away from his Lord (Allah) [Tafsir Al-Qurtubi].(V.29:45) See the footnotes of (Verse 13:28) and also (B) of (Verse 2:152).
  30,22,"And among His Signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the difference of your languages and colours. Verily, in that are indeed signs for men of sound knowledge."
  30,23,"And among His Signs is your sleep{1} by night and by day, and your seeking of His Bounty. Verily, in that are indeed signs for a people who listen.",footnotes:1:(V.23) It is a sign from among the Signs of Allah that a person goes to sleep; the medical world up to now does not know exactly why a person goes to sleep. There are only theories. So this Qur’ân is a miracle from Allah, and not an invented tale as the disbelievers (in the Oneness of Allah) argue.
  30,24,"And among His Signs is that He shows you the lightning, for fear and for hope, and He sends down water (rain) from the sky, and therewith revives the earth after its death. Verily, in that are indeed signs for a people who understand."
  31,7,"And when Our Verses (of the Qur’ân) are recited to such a one, he turns away in pride,{1} as if he heard them not - as if there were deafness in his ear. So announce to him a painful torment.",footnotes:1:(V.7): See the footnote of (V.22:9).
  31,8,"Verily, those who believe (in Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous good deeds, for them are Gardens of Delight (Paradise)."
  31,9,"To abide therein. It is a Promise of Allâh in truth. And He is the All-Mighty, the All-Wise."